what caused panic attacks and depression after open heart surgery some days feel good for several days in a row and then fall back into not wanting to get out of bed help my dad had heart surgery a couple of months ago he started having panic attacks whenever he tried to lay flat in bed the doctor explained that the body was reacting that way because of some fear that the heart might stop beating it is a natural reaction to such a major surgery my dad fell into a bit of depression because he's not able to do everything that he wants to yet if you are on medication you should talk to the doctor about side effects these could be causing problems but you also have to let your body take the time to heal some days your body is not going to want to do much but sleep other days you might have more energy this is totally normal my dad went through this for a few weeks be gentle with yourself and understand that the healing process takes longer than we want it to Stroke Prostate cancer Stomach cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Social rule Anxiety Church of Christ, Scientist Medicine Myocardial infarction Clinical depression Milton H. Erickson Chronic fatigue syndrome Psoriasis Panic attack Scar Traumatic brain injury Sleep Urinary incontinence Out-of-body experience Insomnia Wound healing phases Post-traumatic stress disorder A Course In Miracles YuYu Hakusho Charles Darwin's illness Breastfeeding Childbirth Folic acid Anorexia nervosa Hormone replacement therapy (trans) W.I.T.C.H. Stress (medicine) Adjustable gastric band Grief Drowning Radiation therapy Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Hypnosis Pope John Paul I Natural Hygiene Penis Mattress Amiodarone Clomipramine Shaggy dog story Sternum Knots Landing Shock Boom Town (Doctor Who) Atherosclerosis Transsexuality Child sexuality Diazepam Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Traditional Chinese medicine Spina bifida Daylight saving time Obesity Carpal tunnel syndrome One Tree Hill (TV series) Phoebe Halliwell